article.headline: Western Michigan 65, Ohio 62
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Joe Reitz scored a career-high 31 points and had a game-high nine rebounds to lead Western Michigan to a 65-62 win over Ohio on Sunday. Reitz converted six consecutive free throws in the final minute to preserve the win for the Broncos (10-13, 7-6 Mid-American), who overcame an eight-point deficit in the second half. Ohio's Antonio Chatman missed a 3-point attempt as the buzzer sounded. Western Michigan broke a two-game losing streak and pulled to within one-half game of Northern Illinois in the MAC West title race. Sonny Troutman led Ohio (14-7, 8-5) with 15 points, although he made just one basket in the second half. Chatman added 12 points. The Broncos made 12 of 13 free throws in the second half, including nine straight by Reitz, who was 10-for-12 from the field. Brian Snider added eight points, seven rebounds and a game-high eight assists for Western Michigan. Ohio outrebounded the Broncos 43-36, led by Mychal Green's nine and Jerome Tillman's eight. But the Bobcats' defense of Reitz was hurt when Green and Leon Williams fouled out. Ohio, which began the game with an 0-for-9 shooting slump, made just 29.7 percent of its shots in the second half. Williams, the team's leading scorer, was held to six points -- his first single-digit output in five games. Ohio had beaten Western by 32 points earlier this season in the Bobcats' most lopsided win of the season. But Sunday's loss was Ohio's fourth consecutive at Western. "The curse of Kalamazoo continues for us," Ohio head coach Tom O'Shea said.
